President Trump hosted the third annual Made in America Showcase at the White House, celebrating American manufacturers and their products. He highlighted the growth of the manufacturing industry since he took office, with the addition of 600,000 manufacturing jobs and the resurgence of American-made products. The President also announced an executive order to increase the standards for "Made in America" products, requiring them to have 75% American content and 95% American content for iron and steel. Additionally, President Trump addressed recent controversy surrounding his tweets about four congresswomen, stating that if they are unhappy with the United States, they can leave. He defended his tweets and criticized the congresswomen for their statements and actions, claiming they hate America and have a disdain for Israel.